 <body>
  <h1>HTML style Attribute</h1>
  <p>The style attribute is used to add styles to an element, such as color, font, size, and more.</p>
  <p style="color:green"> This is Style attribute applied on paragraph tag.</p>
   
   <h1>HTML title Attribute</h1>
   <p>The title attribute defines some extra information about an element.</p>
   <p>The value of the title attribute will be displayed as a tooltip when you mouse over the element</p>
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   <p>you can specify the size for any heading with the style attribute, using the CSS font-size property</p>
   <h1 style="font-size:70px">This is a Main Heading</h1>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    <p title="I'm a tooltip">This is a paragraph.</p>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	<p>The "hr" element is used to <br>separate content (or define a change) in an HTML page</p>

	<h2>This is a Heading 1</h2>
	<p>This is a Paragraph 1</p>
	<hr> <!---------hr=Horizontal ruler------->
	<h2>This is a Heading 2</h2>
	<p>This is a paragraph 2</p>

 </body>
